{"id": "EUVD-2022-55286", "enisaUuid": "ada1da05-98a7-3c9c-9544-6576979281ef", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nxfrm: fix refcount leak in __xfrm_policy_check()\n\nThe issue happens on an error path in __xfrm_policy_check(). When the\nfetching process of the object `pols[1]` fails, the function simply\nreturns 0, forgetting to decrement the reference count of `pols[0]`,\nwhich is incremented earlier by either xfrm_sk_policy_lookup() or\nxfrm_policy_lookup(). This may result in memory leaks.\n\nFix it by decreasing the reference count of `pols[0]` in that path.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:41", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T18:31:25", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/18e6b6e2555c93f5ca09f2b85ef1fa025c8accea", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8f94b933103ee1bda119543369cc18a1be5536db", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0769491a8acd3e85ca4c3f65080eac2c824262df", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/63da7a2bbf3f28094920e0b8a17d2571a9bd842d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1305d7d4f35ca6f214a2d23b075aa6a924cff3be", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/26ad2398fe4984f4f6f930bcb3bc9047fa77265b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d66c052879791313f90c0584420f196a038fb8b8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9c9cb23e00ddf45679b21b4dacc11d1ae7961ebe", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50007"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50007"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0d266ae4-8ee2-3867-b7ad-684f6ec1da36", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "0f93ffeb-32e6-341d-98e8-38530c028a9f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.6"}, {"id": "144895e4-5e63-3046-be28-91d19a54dd84", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.140"}, {"id": "2b4aa8da-6f62-3e95-881c-7ed9ee1e4010", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.9.327"}, {"id": "379f032a-8821-3382-b6ac-4074c2986137", "product": {"name": 